main event: An unidentified object was observed for 6 minutes on July 15, 1963, categorized as ECHO 7 - Unknown.
interesting points: The object was observed traveling at high speed and high altitude,It was described as a white object the size of a first magnitude star,The sighting was conducted using ground radar as part of military observation,The object was observed at an elevation of 20 degrees and azimuth of 140 degrees,The investigation concluded that the object was believed to be a satellite.
witness description: Military personnel involved in the observation
